# Ztarknet Design System Rules

## Overview
This document defines the design system and UI/UX patterns used across all Ztarknet applications (website, explorer, web-wallet). All AI agents and developers MUST follow these rules to maintain visual consistency and brand identity.

---

## üé® Color Palette

### Brand Colors (Primary)
```css
--background: #040405        /* Deep black background */
--foreground: #f4f4f6        /* Light text */
--accent: #ff6b1a            /* Ztarknet Orange (primary) */
--accent-strong: #ff8946     /* Brighter orange for emphasis */
--muted: #777c8e             /* Muted text/secondary content */
```

### Surface Colors
```css
--card-bg: rgba(12, 13, 17, 0.85)      /* Semi-transparent card background */
--card-border: rgba(255, 107, 26, 0.4) /* Orange border with transparency */
```

### Usage Guidelines
- **Background**: Always use `#040405` as the main background
- **Accent Orange** (`#ff6b1a`): Use for:
  - Primary CTAs and buttons
  - Links and interactive elements
  - Borders and highlights
  - Brand-related text
- **Text**: 
  - Primary text: `#f4f4f6` (--foreground)
  - Secondary/muted: `#777c8e` (--muted)
- **Transparency**: Always use rgba() for borders and overlays to maintain depth

