## üî§ Typography

### Font Families
```css
--font-sans: 'Space Grotesk', system-ui, sans-serif
--font-mono: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace
```

### Type Scale & Usage

#### Headings
- **Hero H1**: `clamp(2.75rem, 5vw, 3.8rem)` - line-height: 1.1, tracking: tight
- **Section H2**: `2.5rem - 3rem` - font-weight: bold, tracking: tight
- **Subsection H3**: `1.5rem - 2rem` - font-weight: semibold

#### Body Text
- **Large**: `1.125rem` (18px) - use for hero descriptions
- **Base**: `1rem` (16px) - default body text
- **Small**: `0.875rem` (14px) - secondary content
- **Tiny**: `0.75rem` (12px) - labels, metadata

#### Code/Monospace
- Always use `font-mono` (JetBrains Mono) for:
  - Addresses, hashes, technical identifiers
  - Code blocks
  - Numeric data (block heights, transaction IDs)

### Text Styling Rules
```css
/* Accent text with glow */
.accent-text {
  color: var(--accent);
  text-shadow: 0 0 18px rgba(255, 107, 26, 0.45);
}

/* Eyebrow/Label style */
.eyebrow {
  text-transform: uppercase;
  tracking: 0.2em; /* widest */
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  color: rgba(255, 107, 26, 0.7);
}
```

